PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773648269
OL,3,CLabour MPs urge prime minister to save
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FHe has written: "A small number of
OL,7,Fpeers have been using procedural
OL,8,Ftactics to block the Bill in the House
OL,9,Fof Lords and it now appears very
OL,10,Flikely that they will prevent it
OL,11,Freturning to the Commons before the
OL,12,Fend of this session.
OL,14,F"While we fully respect the
OL,15,Fgovernment's neutrality on the
OL,16,Fprinciple of assisted dying, we are
OL,17,Fconfident that you would agree with us
OL,18,Fthat we cannot be neutral on the
OL,19,Ffundamental democratic principle that
OL,20,Fit is for the elected House of Commons
OL,21,Fto decide on this matter.
OL,26,@nD@QOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773648269
OL,3,CLabour MPs urge prime minister to save
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,F"Our constituents, in every part of
OL,7,Fthe country, strongly support a change
OL,8,Fin the law and it is clear to us that
OL,9,Fthe issue must be resolved sooner
OL,10,Frather than later.
OL,12,F"Our ask is simple: That, whether or
OL,13,Fnot the Bill returns through the
OL,14,Fprivate members' bill ballot after the
OL,15,FKings Speech, time will be found for
OL,16,FParliament to come to a decision in
OL,17,Fthe next session.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773648269
OL,3,CLabour MPs urge prime minister to save
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,F"It would remain a conscience issue
OL,7,Ffor MPs, the government's neutrality
OL,8,Fwould be maintained, and it need not
OL,9,Ftake up time reserved for government
OL,10,Fbusiness."
OL,12,FITV News understands that the bill's
OL,13,Fsupporters want the government to make
OL,14,Ftime for an assisted dying bill to
OL,15,Freturn in the next session of
OL,16,Fparliament - in other words, after the
OL,17,FKing's Speech in May.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
