CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773648269
OL,3,CLabour MPs urge prime minister to save
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FThis could be via another private
OL,7,Fmembers' bill, where a backbench MP
OL,8,Fmight bring the same bill again in the
OL,9,Fhope that this time it passes the
OL,10,FLords.
OL,12,FHowever, supporters are relying on
OL,13,Fluck, as MPs are drawn from a ballot
OL,14,Fat random, which determines who gets
OL,15,Fto bring forward a bill.
OL,17,FThey hope that a supporter will be
OL,18,Fdrawn near the top of the ballot, but
OL,19,Fthere are no guarantees.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
