PN,31910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1773648269
OL,3,CLabour MPs urge prime minister to save
OL,4,Cthe assisted dying bill
OL,6,FSo far, Number 10 has refused to
OL,7,Fintervene, having always taken a
OL,8,Fneutral position on the bill. The
OL,9,Fensuing debate has become polarised,
OL,10,Fwith Labour MPs and cabinet members
OL,11,Fsplit on the issue.
OL,13,FOn Tuesday, Scotland will vote on a
OL,14,Fseparate bill in Holyrood which would
OL,15,Flegalise assisted dying there. The
OL,16,Fvote is believed to be on a knife edge.
OL,18,FJersey and the Isle of Man have
OL,19,Falready become the first two places in
OL,20,Fthe British Isles to pass a law
OL,21,Flegalising assisted dying.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
